# MedTek — Complete Project Analysis & Walkthrough

## 1. What is MedTek?

**MedTek** is a full-stack **AI-powered medical ecosystem** application built with **Flutter** (frontend) and **Node.js/Express** (backend), backed by a **PostgreSQL** database. It connects **patients**, **doctors**, **lab assistants**, and **drivers** into a unified healthcare platform with features including:

- AI-powered medical triage (Gemini + custom Ollama/OptGPT models)
- Appointment booking with map-based hospital discovery
- Doctor verification & onboarding
- Lab test management workflow
- Ride booking to hospitals
- AI pill identification & drug interaction checking
- Medical reports management
- Multilingual voice support (English, Hindi, Telugu, Tamil, Arabic)

---

## 2. Technology Stack

| Layer | Technology |
|---|---|
| **Frontend** | Flutter (Dart), Provider state management |
| **Backend** | Node.js, Express.js |
| **Database** | PostgreSQL (via `pg` Pool) |
| **AI — Chat** | Google Gemini 2.5 Flash (via `@google/generative-ai`) |
| **AI — Triage** | Ollama running OptGPT-4:latest (local LLM) |
| **AI — Vision** | Gemini 2.5 Flash (pill identification) |
| **Maps** | Mapbox Maps Flutter, Google Maps Flutter |
| **Media** | Cloudinary (image uploads), Multer (file handling) |
| **Auth** | JWT + bcrypt password hashing |
| **Security** | Helmet.js, express-rate-limit, CORS |
| **Voice** | `speech_to_text`, `flutter_tts` |
| **HTTP Client** | Dio (Flutter), fetch API (Node.js) |
| **Storage** | SharedPreferences (local session) |
| **Containerization** | Docker + docker-compose |

---

## 3. Architecture Overview

```mermaid
graph TD
    subgraph Flutter App
        A[EntryGate] --> B{User Role?}
        B -->|patient| C[PatientDashboard]
        B -->|doctor| D[DoctorDashboard]
        B -->|lab_assistant| E[LabDashboard]
        B -->|not logged in| F[AuthPage]
    end

    subgraph Backend API
        G[Express Server :4000]
        G --> H[Auth Routes]
        G --> I[Hospital Routes]
        G --> J[Doctor Routes]
        G --> K[Appointment Routes]
        G --> L[AI Routes - Gemini/Ollama]
        G --> M[Lab Routes]
        G --> N[Medical Report Routes]
        G --> O[Ride Routes]
        G --> P[Verification Routes]
        G --> Q[Triage Routes]
    end

    subgraph External Services
        R[Google Gemini API]
        S[Ollama - OptGPT-4]
        T[Mapbox API]
        U[Cloudinary CDN]
        V[PostgreSQL DB]
    end

    C --> G
    D --> G
    E --> G
    L --> R
    L --> S
    G --> V
```

