## 4. Database Schema

The database uses **8 sequential SQL migrations**:

### Core Tables

| Table | Purpose | Key Columns |
|---|---|---|
| `users` | All user accounts | [id](file:///c:/Users/botch/New_app/MedTek/AI_Flutter_Applications-medtek/medtek/lib/services/api_service.dart#662-669), `name`, `email`, `password_hash`, `role`, `profile_picture`, `assigned_hospital_id` |
| `hospitals` | Hospital registry | [id](file:///c:/Users/botch/New_app/MedTek/AI_Flutter_Applications-medtek/medtek/lib/services/api_service.dart#662-669), `name`, `address`, `city`, `latitude`, `longitude`, `phone` |
| `doctors` | Doctor profiles (linked to users) | `user_id`, `hospital_id`, `specialization`, `experience_years`, `about`, `verified`, `rating`, `nmc_number`, `verification_points`, `verification_details` |
| `appointments` | Patient-doctor appointments | `user_id`, `doctor_id`, `hospital_id`, `status`, `scheduled_at` |
| `medical_reports` | Consultation records + lab orders | `doctor_id`, `patient_id`, `appointment_id`, `diagnosis`, `prescription`, `lab_tests`, `lab_tests_json`, `lab_tests_count`, `report_status` |
| `rides` | Transport bookings | `rider_id`, `driver_id`, `pickup_lat/lng`, `drop_lat/lng`, `distance_km`, `estimated_fare`, `status`, [pin](file:///c:/Users/botch/New_app/MedTek/AI_Flutter_Applications-medtek/medtek/lib/src/triage_page.dart#1054-1123) |
| `doctor_reviews` | Patient reviews of doctors | `doctor_id`, `patient_name`, `rating` (1-5), `comment` |
| `hospital_doctors` | Many-to-many link | `user_id`, `hospital_id` |

### User Roles
- `patient` — End users seeking medical care
- `doctor` — Medical practitioners
- `lab_assistant` — Hospital lab staff
- `driver` — Transport service providers
- `admin` — System administrators

